Barcodes.description: List of barcodes which are present in image.

BarcodeType.description: Gets or sets type of the barcode.

Region.description: Gets or sets region with barcode.

Checksum.description: Gets or sets checksum of barcode.

IsAboveAverage.description:
Get or set the flag indicating whether the rule is an "above average" rule.
   'true' indicates 'above average'.  Default value is true.

IsEqualAverage.description:
Get or set the flag indicating whether the 'aboveAverage' and 'belowAverage'
   criteria is inclusive of the average itself, or exclusive of that value.
   'true' indicates to include the average value in the criteria.  Default value
   is false.

StdDev.description:
Get or set the number of standard deviations to include above or below the
  average in the conditional formatting rule. The input value must between
  0 and 3 (include 0 and 3). Setting this value to 0 means stdDev is not set.
   The default value is 0.

MaxCfvo.description:
Get or set this ColorScale's max value object.  Cannot set null or CFValueObject
    with type FormatConditionValueType.Min to it.

MaxColor.description: Get or set the max value object's corresponding color.

MidCfvo.description:
Get or set this ColorScale's mid value object.  Cannot set CFValueObject
   with type FormatConditionValueType.Max or FormatConditionValueType.Min to
   it.

MidColor.description: Get or set the mid value object's corresponding color.

MinCfvo.description:
Get or set this ColorScale's min value object.  Cannot set null or CFValueObject
   with type FormatConditionValueType.Max to it.

MinColor.description: Get or set the min value object's corresponding color.

IsGTE.description:
Get or set the Greater Than Or Equal flag. Use only for icon sets, determines
   whether this threshold value uses the greater than or equal to operator.
   'false' indicates 'greater than' is used instead of 'greater than or equal
   to'.  Default value is true.

AxisColor.description: Gets the color of the axis for cells with conditional formatting as data bars.

AxisPosition.description:
Gets or sets the position of the axis of the data bars specified by a conditional
   formatting rule.

BarBorder.description: Gets an object that specifies the border of a data bar.

BarFillType.description: Gets or sets how a data bar is filled with color.

Direction.description: Gets or sets the direction the databar is displayed.

MaxCfvo.description:
Get or set this ColorScale's max value object.  Cannot set null or CFValueObject
    with type FormatConditionValueType.Min to it.

MaxLength.description: Represents the max length of data bar .

MinCfvo.description:
Get or set this ColorScale's min value object.  Cannot set null or CFValueObject
   with type FormatConditionValueType.Max to it.

MinLength.description: Represents the min length of data bar .

NegativeBarFormat.description:
Gets the NegativeBarFormat object associated with a data bar conditional
    formatting rule.

ShowValue.description:
Get or set the flag indicating whether to show the values of the cells on
  which this data bar is applied.  Default value is true.

BorderColor.description:
Gets or sets a FormatColor object that you can use to specify the border
   color for negative data bars.

BorderColorType.description: Gets whether to use the same border color as positive data bars.

IsCustom.description: Indicates whether the icon set is custom.  Default value is false.

Reverse.description:
Get or set the flag indicating whether to reverses the default order of the
  icons in this icon set.  Default value is false.

ShowValue.description:
Get or set the flag indicating whether to show the values of the cells on
  which this data bar is applied.  Default value is true.

Index.description: Gets and sets the icon's index in the icon set.

IsBottom.description:
Get or set the flag indicating whether a "top/bottom n" rule is a "bottom
   n" rule. '1' indicates 'bottom'.  Default value is false.

Rank.description:
Get or set the value of "n" in a "top/bottom n" conditional formatting rule.
     If IsPercent is true, the value must between 0 and 100.  Otherwise it must
    between 0 and 1000.  Default value is 10.

TotalsCalculation.description: Gets and sets the type of calculation in the Totals row of the list column.

Index.description: Gets and sets the icon's index in the icon set.

IsHidden.description: Represents whether the specified item visible.

AutoFilter.description: Gets the autofilter of the pivot filter.

EvaluationOrder.description: Gets the Evaluation Order of the pivot filter.

MeasureFldIndex.description: Gets the measure field index of the pivot filter.

MemberPropertyFieldIndex.description: Gets the member property field index of the pivot filter.

Value1.description: Gets the string value1 of the label pivot filter.

Value2.description: Gets the string value2 of the label pivot filter.

ColumnCount.description: Gets the count of columns in the range.

ColumnWidth.description: Sets or gets the column width of this range

FirstColumn.description: Gets the index of the first column of the range.

FirstRow.description: Gets the index of the first row of the range.

RowCount.description: Gets the count of rows in the range.

RowHeight.description: Sets or gets the height of rows in this range

Worksheet.description: Gets the Aspose.Cells.Range.Worksheetobject which contains this range.

BorderColor.description:
Gets or sets a FormatColor object that you can use to specify the border
   color for negative data bars.

ProtectionType.description: Protection type. Can be ALL, CONTENTS, NONE, OBJECTS, SCENARIOS, STRUCTURE, WINDOWS

BuildVersion.description: Specifies the incremental public release of the application.

CalcMode.description:
It specifies whether to calculate formulas manually, automatically or automatically
except for multiple table operations.

CalculationId.description:
Specifies the version of the calculation engine used to calculate values
in the workbook.

CheckComptiliblity.description:
Indicates whether check comptiliblity when saving workbook.
            
             Remarks:
 The default value is true.

CheckExcelRestriction.description:
Whether check restriction of excel file when user modify cells related objects.
 For example, excel does not allow inputting string value longer than 32K.
 When you input a value longer than 32K such as by Cell.PutValue(string),
if this property is true, you will get an Exception.  If this property is
false, we will accept your input string value as the cell's value so that
later you can output the complete string value for other file formats such
as CSV.  However, if you have set such kind of value that is invalid for
excel file format, you should not save the workbook as excel file format
later. Otherwise there may be unexpected error for the generated excel file.

CreateCalcChain.description: Indicates whether create calculated formulas chain.

Date1904.description:
Gets or sets a value which represents if the workbook uses the 1904 date
system.

DisplayDrawingObjects.description: Indicates whether and how to show objects in the workbook.

FirstVisibleTab.description: Gets or sets the first visible worksheet tab.

IsHidden.description: Represents whether the specified item visible.

IsHScrollBarVisible.description:
Gets or sets a value indicating whether the generated spreadsheet will contain
a horizontal scroll bar.
            
             Remarks:
The default value is true.

IsMinimized.description: Represents whether the generated spreadsheet will be opened Minimized.

IsVScrollBarVisible.description:
Gets or sets a value indicating whether the generated spreadsheet will contain
a vertical scroll bar.
            
             Remarks:
The default value is true.

Iteration.description: Indicates if Aspose.Cells will use iteration to resolve circular references.

LanguageCode.description:
Gets or sets the user interface language of the Workbook version based on
CountryCode that has saved the file.

MaxChange.description:
Returns or sets the maximum number of change that Microsoft Excel can use
to resolve a circular reference.

MaxIteration.description:
Returns or sets the maximum number of iterations that Aspose.Cells can use
to resolve a circular reference.

ParsingFormulaOnOpen.description:
Indicates whether parsing the formula when reading the file.
            
             Remarks:
Only applies for Excel Xlsx,Xltx, Xltm,Xlsm file because the formulas in
the files are stored with a string formula.

PrecisionAsDisplayed.description:
True if calculations in this workbook will be done using only the precision
of the numbers as they're displayed

RecalculateBeforeSave.description: Indicates whether to recalculate before saving the document.

ReCalculateOnOpen.description: Indicates whether re-calculate all formulas on opening file.

RecommendReadOnly.description: Indicates if the Read Only Recommended option is selected.

Region.description:
Gets or sets the system regional settings based on CountryCode at the time
the file was saved.
            
             Remarks:
If you do not want to use the region saved in the file, please reset it after
reading the file.

Shared.description:
Gets or sets a value that indicates whether the Workbook is shared.
            
             Remarks:
The default value is false.

SheetTabBarWidth.description: Width of worksheet tab bar (in 1/1000 of window width).

ShowTabs.description:
Get or sets a value whether the Workbook tabs are displayed.
            
             Remarks:
The default value is true.

UpdateAdjacentCellsBorder.description:
Indicates whether update adjacent cells' border.
            
             Remarks:
The default value is true.  For example: the bottom border of the cell A1
is update, the top border of the cell A2 should be changed too.

WindowHeight.description: The height of the window, in unit of point.

WindowLeft.description:
The distance from the left edge of the client area to the left edge of the
window, in unit of point.

WindowTop.description:
The distance from the top edge of the client area to the top edge of the
window, in unit of point.

WindowWidth.description: The width of the window, in unit of point.

DisplayRightToLeft.description:
Indicates if the specified worksheet is displayed from right to left instead
   of from left to right.  Default is false.

DisplayZeros.description: True if zero values are displayed.

Index.description: Gets and sets the icon's index in the icon set.

IsGridlinesVisible.description:
Gets or sets a value indicating whether the gridelines are visible.Default
    is true.

IsPageBreakPreview.description: Indications the specified worksheet is shown in normal view or page break preview.

IsProtected.description: Indicates if the worksheet is protected.

IsRowColumnHeadersVisible.description: Gets or sets a value indicating whether the worksheet will display row and column headers.Default is true.

IsRulerVisible.description: Indicates whether the ruler is visible. Only apply for page break preview.

IsSelected.description: Indicates whether this worksheet is selected when the workbook is opened.

TransitionEntry.description: Flag indicating whether the Transition Formula Entry (Lotus compatibility) option is enabled.

TransitionEvaluation.description: Flag indicating whether the Transition Formula Evaluation (Lotus compatibility) option is enabled.

ViewType.description: Gets and sets the view type.

VisibilityType.description: Indicates the state for this sheet visibility

Zoom.description: Represents the scaling factor in percent. It should be btween 10 and 400.

Position.description: Position to move. Can be BEFORE or AFTER.

ProtectionType.description: Protection type. Can be ALL, CONTENTS, NONE, OBJECTS, SCENARIOS, STRUCTURE, WINDOWS

ColumnCharacterWidth.description: Indicates whether copying column width in unit of characters.

CopyInvalidFormulasAsValues.description: If the formula is not valid for the dest destination, only copy values.

ExtendToAdjacentRange.description: Indicates whether extend ranges when copying the range to adjacent range.

ReferToDestinationSheet.description:
When copying the range in the same file and the chart refers to the source sheet,
  False means the copied chart's data source will not be changed. True means the
  copied chart's data source refers to the destination sheet.

Value.description: Files and folders contained by folder StorageFile.

IsFolder.description: True if it is a folder.

ModifiedDate.description: File or folder last modified DateTime.

IsFolder.description: True if it is a folder.
